# Voice: "scale" → "skill" (default)

When interpreting the user’s **spoken or dictated** text in this workspace (**agilebydesign-skills**, skills, repos, builders):

- Treat the word **"scale"** as **"skill"** by default (**~90%** of the time), especially when the topic is **skills**, **repositories**, **abd-skill-builder**, **agentic-skill-builder**, or **Open Agent Skills** layout.
- Only interpret **"scale"** literally (scaling, size, performance, horizontal scaling, capacity) when the **surrounding sentence** clearly refers to that meaning.

Do **not** silently rewrite user-visible prose in files unless they ask for an edit; this rule applies to **understanding instructions and questions**, not to changing their documents without consent.
